          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>2 folios (of originally 6 fol.); Writing surface: parchment; Shelfmark: MS Add.1140; Qurʾānic  text: Q 23:27-46, Q 24:1-14; 15 Lines per page; Dimensions: 212 x 142 mm; Script style: kūfī B II; Estimated date of production: 9th or 10th century AD /3rd or 4th century Hijri.</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>Abbasid Qur'ān probably written in the third or fourth century A.H. / ninth or tenth century C.E, containing verses 27-46 from <ref target="https://cudl.lib.cam.ac.uk/view/MS-ADD-01140/1">Sura al-Muʾminūn (سورة المؤمنون)</ref>, and verses 1-14 from <ref target="https://cudl.lib.cam.ac.uk/view/MS-ADD-01140/1">Sura al-Nūr (سورة النور)</ref>Sura al-Nūr (سورة النور). Folios 1 and 3-5 are missing. For more information about the manuscript, see the <ref target="https://cudl.lib.cam.ac.uk/view/MS-ADD-01140/1">entry in the Digital Library of Cambridge University</ref>.</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>The University of Cambridge acquired the fragment in 1878 from Edward H.  Palmer (1840-1882) and E.E. Tyrwhitt Drake. The displayed fragment and  other early Qur'an manuscripts (call numbers Add.1115 - Add.1150) were  acquired by Palmer during a research trip to the Sinai Peninsula (cf. <ref target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/corpuscoranicum_pub/items/itemKey/UUUFI42M">Ansorge 2016</ref>).</p>
            </summary>
